<title>USA: ADM to buy facilities in Brazil, Paraguay.</title>
<headline>ADM to buy facilities in Brazil, Paraguay.</headline>
<dateline>DECATUR, Ill. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Archer Daniels Midland Co said Friday it entered into an agreement in principle with Glencore Grain Holding to purchase Glencore's grain handling facilities in Brazil and Paraguay.</p>
<p>These assets include two terminal elevators in the Ports of Tubarao and Santos, nine owned interior elevators and 23 leased interior elevators in Brazil, as well as 23 owned interior elevators in Paraguay.</p>
<p>ADM did not disclose the amount of the investment.  </p>
<p>ADM said the transaction is subject to a final agreement and is expected to close in August, 1997.</p>
<p>Glencore Grain is a division of Swiss-based Glencore Ltd.</p>
<p>((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
